<br><b><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#4681BD" weight="bold">.:My Basketball IQ: 2!:.</font></b><br>
<small><font size="1" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0F7B66">Wednesday, February 12 2003</font></small><br><br>

<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><font color="#FFFFFF">Ever feel like you could stare or try at something and it wouldn't come to you? This is how I feel about organized basketball at the moment. Something just not clicking. Feeling lost. Not a good feeling at all. Actually I think its a matter of confidence, when I play with people I know, I seem to know what to do and how to do it. But then the pressure of people I dont know and expectations at practice seems to get to me. Its quite sad, this rarely happens elsewhere, cept maybe at work. Need to fix this fast cuz its frustrating me to no end this evening. </P><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY>
</p></font></font>
