<br><b><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#4681BD" weight="bold">.:Tired, Sore and well Beaten Up:.</font></b><br>
<small><font size="1" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0F7B66">Friday, February 07 2003</font></small><br><br>

<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><font color="#FFFFFF">This week I started playing with the scout/practice team for the girls basketball team at Columbia. I must say, this has been the best workout I've recieved in a looooooooong time. Chasing some of the point/shooting guards around the court is extremely tiring. It doesn't help that Blye gave me the King Kong of Charlie Horses the other day, making me not quite so limber. In any case, being beaten up by girls on a daily basis isn't all that bad. Managed to learn a lot, having had NO organized basketball experience up till this point. Meeting new people is also fun too. So as of now, Tuesdays through Thursday involves much banging and physical play with sweaty females... @.@</P><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY>
DE Shaw Interview, two tuesdays from now. Should be interesting. Shorts and Jeans are often their dress code, so isn't that nice. </P><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY>
<BR></p></font></font>
