<br><b><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#4681BD" weight="bold">.:Looooong Looooooong Weeks:.</font></b><br>
<small><font size="1" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0F7B66">Sunday, January 26 2003</font></small><br><br>

<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><font color="#FFFFFF">Where to begin? </P><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY>
I apologize for the lack of updates, it's been a long 2.5 weeks. First there was the matter of spending all the final hours of winter break in joyous celebration. (i.e. spending hours watching strange movies at Esthers house till 7am for an entire week) The end of vacation culminated in an evening of overindulging in alcoholic beverages... Mike's Birthday. 15 Shots in 40 minutes... It was quite a stupifying achievement to be honest. They could make a movie of it. Zero to Gone in 40 minutes. Apparently members of the inner circle wish to make this a new tradition for birthdays. At this rate, this tradition will either die, or one of us will attempting to follow suit. Im betting on the latter.</P><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY>
Moving back into school wasn't such a horrible transition. I had expected dreading being back but as of late being at the dorm, on campus hasn't been all bad. With the exception of being Xed-over 5-6 times on thursday while playing basketball and essentially embarrassed in front of alot of people, the week has gone pretty well. At this point I dont actually have any classes I am signed up for on tuesdays and thursdays, and my schedule on M-W is pretty light. I do wonder if I am slacking this way, but then again, I don't wanna stress too much when finals come around. Imagine the years of my life I am preserving in this fashion. Stress during finals weeks must be the cause of loss for many person-years of lifetime accross the nation. It cannot be good.</P><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY>
The new plan for my self edification is to randomly pick and choose people to follow into class and see if I can learn anything interesting. I figure, I am more inclined to actually learn and attend classes where I dont have to do work. It will keep things refreshing and new. Strange huh? When I dont need to go to class I want to, and when I have to, well I sleep and play basketball. Freedom is a wonderful thing.</P><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY>
In other news, Katie came down to stay. She got to meet all my crazy friends and family. A little karaoke, some of the met, some shopping and just all around fun. Superbowl sunday coming up too! This means Popeyes Chicken and Cajun rice at Mike and Willy's. I entered into a superbowl pool at work too. Oakland 4's and Tampa Bay 6's.... Hopefully the result of the game will be this: Oakland 14 Tampa Bay 6 in the first quarter! Then the defensive coordinators take over keeping the score 14 - 6 the rest of the game! </P><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY>
When I get a chance tomorrow I'll fix up some of the missing photo albums, finish up my grad school apps and then work on the website hopefully. I am also determined to learn some korean, japanese and some other weird and not necessarily applicable skill sets. </p></font></font>
